        <type>int(*</type>
        <definition>int(* sensor_decoder_api::decode) (const uint8_t *buffer, struct sensor_chan_spec chan_spec, uint32_t *fit, uint16_t max_count, void *data_out)</definition>
        <argsstring>)(const uint8_t *buffer, struct sensor_chan_spec chan_spec, uint32_t *fit, uint16_t max_count, void *data_out)</argsstring>
        <name>decode</name>
        <qualifiedname>sensor_decoder_api::decode</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Decode up to <computeroutput>max_count</computeroutput> frames specified by <computeroutput>chan_spec</computeroutput> from the <computeroutput>buffer</computeroutput>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Sample showing the process of decoding at most <computeroutput>MAX_FRAMES</computeroutput> for each distance sensor channel. The frame iterator is reset for each new channel to allow the full history of each channel to be decoded.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".c"><codeline><highlight class="keywordflow">for</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>(</highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">int</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>i<sp/>=<sp/>0;<sp/>i<sp/>&lt;<sp/>NUM_DISTANCE_CHANNELS;<sp/>i++)<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>fit<sp/>=<sp/>0;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>decoder-&gt;decode(buffer,<sp/>{<ref refid="group__sensor__interface_1ggaaa1b502bc029b10d7b23b0a25ef4e934ad46d1495990a86fa7e2ab5bbe5338e08" kindref="member">SENSOR_CHAN_DISTANCE</ref>,<sp/>i},<sp/>&amp;fit,<sp/>MAX_FRAMES,<sp/>out);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">buffer</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Buffer provided on the RTIO context </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">chan_spec</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Channel specification to decode </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="inout">fit</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Current frame iterator </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">max_count</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Maximum number of frames to decode </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="out">data_out</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Decoded data</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Number of frames that were decoded </para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-EINVAL</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Invalid parameters or unsupported channel </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-ENODATA</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Requested data type not present in the frame </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
